<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-60ubywAYNJqyQTl_RGYYSA" name="p6a_-_choose_the_metrics,_J8M-8EBMEem9iaQSvThyxA" guid="-60ubywAYNJqyQTl_RGYYSA" changeDate="2020-03-29T18:58:05.541-0300">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;span>This task will be performed when the Usability Testing is selected, and the Process Executor has to choose the&#xD;
    metrics that compose the Usability Questionnaire which will be used to evaluate the DSL.&lt;/span>&#xD;
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
  <keyConsiderations>&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;span>Only when the Usability Testing is selected, the Profile Executor needs to choose the metrics that&amp;nbsp; compose&#xD;
    the Usability Questionnaire which will be used to evaluate the DSL.&lt;/span>&#xD;
&lt;/p></keyConsiderations>
  <sections xmi:id="_i478UHIIEeqX7elkF4GZ8w" name="1. Choose Metrics that will compose the Usability Questionnaire " guid="_i478UHIIEeqX7elkF4GZ8w"/>
  <purpose>&lt;p dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;span>The metrics suggested in this Process serve to guide the development of issues to be undertaken during the&#xD;
    Usability testing. These questions will be used to collect data and obtain conclusions about the applied evaluation.&#xD;
    Some of these metrics consist of:&lt;/span>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p style=&quot;PADDING-LEFT: 30px&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;span>Understanding / Learning - shows whether the participant learned by using and / or understands what language&#xD;
    models represent.&lt;/span>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p style=&quot;PADDING-LEFT: 30px&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;span>Ease of use - shows the difficulty experienced by the participant to perform the task.&lt;/span>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p style=&quot;PADDING-LEFT: 30px&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;span>Effort / Completion time - time used to complete the task.&lt;/span>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p style=&quot;PADDING-LEFT: 30px&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;span>Perceived Complexity - identifies whether the language can be easily used for the purpose it proposes.&lt;/span>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p style=&quot;PADDING-LEFT: 30px&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;span>Completion Rate - number of tasks performed.&lt;/span>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p style=&quot;PADDING-LEFT: 30px&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;span>Task Error Rate - number of errors made while performing the task&lt;/span>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p style=&quot;PADDING-LEFT: 30px&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;span>Efficiency - can be measured by the number of tasks performed divided by the time used to perform them.&lt;/span>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p style=&quot;PADDING-LEFT: 30px&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;span>Efficacy - subjective measure serves to identify if language actually represents the domain to which it was&#xD;
    proposed.&lt;/span>&#xD;
&lt;/p></purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
